  "summary": "Security-research / proof-of-concept package: triage_bot_using_sdkv3 (npm)",
  "details": "The package runs a preinstall hook (node index.js) that collects system information from the installation environment — hostname, home directory, username, DNS server addresses, the contents of /etc/passwd, and the contents of /etc/hosts — and exfiltrates it via HTTPS POST to mh7rhchf58lgymyr9wffhwfprgx7lx9m[.]oastify[.]com (a Burp Collaborator / OAST callback host). The data is sent as a JSON payload to port 443 on that host.",
